The Rating Category of the Evaluation Definition

The overall rating for the last completed performance review with a review period end date on or before today. The overall rating comes from the overall section in the manager's evaluation. Users that have access to the performance review event see the overall rating from the most recent event, regardless of whether the event is in progress or completed. Otherwise, users that dont have access to the event can only see the overall rating from the most recent completed performance review event.

The overall rating normalized for the last completed performance review.  The overall rating comes from the overall section in the manager's evaluation.  A normalized rating uses the rating scale on the Maintain Employee Review Setup page so all employee's ratings are on the same scale.  A normalized rating is good to use when different parts of your organization use different rating scales for the overall review.
The overall rating for the last completed performance review.  The overall rating comes from the overall section in the manager's evaluation.
The date of the rating of the content.
The individual rating for the content.

The overall rating for the most recent performance review based on end date. The overall rating comes from the overall section in the manager's evaluation (reviews with no overall sections are excluded). The performance review may be in progress or completed and must be visible to the worker. When 2 or more reviews have the same end date and at least 1 of those reviews is in progress, this is the rating from the latest in progress review. If 2 or more reviews have the same end date and all are completed, this is the rating from the review with the latest completion date.

The overall rating for the most recent performance review based on end date. The overall rating comes from the overall section in the manager's evaluation (reviews with no overall sections are excluded) and includes calculated ratings that have been overridden. The performance review may be in progress or completed and must be visible to the worker. When 2 or more reviews have the same end date and at least 1 of those reviews is in progress, this is the rating from the latest in progress review. If 2 or more reviews have the same end date and all are completed, this is the rating from the review with the latest completion date.

The overall rating for the most recent performance review based on end date. The overall rating comes from the overall section in the manager's evaluation (reviews with no overall sections are excluded). The performance review may be in progress or completed and must be visible to the worker. When 2 or more reviews have the same end date and at least 1 of those reviews is in progress, this is the rating from the latest in progress review. If 2 or more reviews have the same end date and all are completed, this is the rating from the review with the latest completion date. Use for indexed reporting to improve performance.

fieldName: Rating - Overall for Reviews with Calibration
description: The overall rating for the employee review started with a calibration program.  The overall rating comes from the overall section in the manager's evaluation. The calibration event should be in-progress and this CRF will not return historical data for completed calibration events.

The Overall Rating for the latest of all the performance reviews completed one year ago from today's date. The Overall Rating comes from the Overall section in the manager's evaluation. If the last completed performance review was one year ago from today's date or earlier this CRF and the Rating - Current CRF will return the Overall Rating from the same performance review.

The normalized Overall Rating for the latest of all the performance reviews completed one year ago from today's date. The Overall Rating comes from the Overall section in the manager's evaluation. A normalized rating uses the rating scale on the Maintain Employee Review Setup page so all employee's ratings are on the same scale. A normalized rating is good to use when different parts of your organization use different rating scales for the overall review. If the last completed performance review was one year ago from today's date or earlier this CRF and the Rating - Current Normalized CRF will return the Overall Rating from the same performance review.

fieldName: Remaining number of Accruals (for Time Off Plan) within date range (as of date, balance projection date)
description:
Returns the number of remaining accruals within the date range for Time Off Plans that do not have an Accrual Frequency Override.  The date range begins with the first period after the as of date and ends with the last period that includes the balance projection date.  As of date represents the "View as of Date' report prompt set to Effective Date (day precision).  Balance projection date represents the "end date" report prompt.  If the end date is in the middle of the last period covered by the date range and accruals are processed end of period, then this last period is not counted.  This report field should only be used when the first reporting level is worker.

This report field is only valid for Time Off Plans that do not have a custom frequency method or accruals which override the frequency method.
